_Values: I can almost hear their tummies rumbling! If you don’t make a deal soon you might end up as dinner
As you can see, there are 3 hungry tigers watching your every move. Fortunately for you, I have 10 pieces of meat to be shared between the 3 tigers.
Well, let's hear it then! How many steaks should the Blue Tiger receive?
Oh dear… you’re looking tastier by the second! Care to choose again my dear little snack.
And how many should the Orange Tiger get?
Oh dear… you’re looking tastier by the second! Care to choose again my dear little snack.
Well well well, aren’t we a smarty pants then! Looks like you live to see another day!
Oh dear… you’re looking tastier by the second! Care to choose again my dear little snack.

The downside is that they can’t come to an agreement as to how much they should each have. You will need to use your bargaining skills to divide the pieces between the 3 to pass through this challenge.
Here’s a little hint: the tiger with the most steaks blocks the passageway that allows you to continue on your journey.
So think carefully and make sure you bargain with each of them by speaking to them until they can’t tell you anything new. If you don’t get the answer you want, try again!
Once you think you know the answer, come let me know.
Please… I’m just asking for a day...
Please don’t let this happen. I’ll do anything… give anything for a bit more time. Just one more day...
It sometimes just inevitable… no matter what you’re willing to sacrifice...

The Sorrow shadows appear when a person is in their darkest hour. It shows when a person feels as though they may be swallowed up whole by the turbulent sea of emotions they have crashing in their heart.
Bargaining is the fourth stage, you might be willing to do anything to change what’s happening. But you need to understand that bargaining is only skin deep and sometimes events are inevitable.
We hear your begging and pleading… does it fall on deaf ears? Sometimes you have to accept the inevitable...
Don’t be so rude! How could you expect me to have any less?!
Jeez! You push a hard bargain young lady. But fine, I’ll accept a few less
I refuse to have the same as any other tiger
We hear your begging and pleading... does it fall on deaf ears? Sometimes you have to accept the inevitable...
Woah, less?! Ok but I have to have more than the Green Tiger!
I want more than the Blue Tiger too!
We hear your begging and pleading... does it fall on deaf ears? Sometimes you have to accept the inevitable...
My final offer is at least 4! I won’t accept anything less!
Excuse me! But don’t you think you’re being a little demanding?
Fine… I’ll settle for a little less than all
You seem confused. I’ll tell you one last time…
